    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "Java <i>CAN</i> &quot;work in VSCode&quot;.  But if you&#39;re &quot;not familiar&quot; with &quot;things such as bin, src, and classpath&quot; ,,, then trust me.  You&#39;ll probably be <i>MUCH</i> happier and productive in a &quot;Java friendly&quot; IDE like IntelliJ, Netbeans or (my favorite) Eclipse.  My &quot;guess&quot;? Your &quot;Problem_001_MultiplesOf3And5.class&quot; file needs to be inside directory &quot;Solved_Problems&quot;.  You need to run Java <i>ABOVE</i> that directory, and you need to <i>INCLUDE</i> it in your classpath.  It sounds like the VSCode debugger is doing this ... but you&#39;re not."
